Schedule Messages for Later Delivery
====================================

Queued messages can be delayed by providing `schedule` frontmatter instructions:


- **after:** time until the message can be sent.**after:** time until the message can be sent.
- **delay:** time duration added to `after` or current time.**delay:** time duration added to `after` or current time.
- **step:** time duration added for each recipient.**step:** time duration added for each recipient.
- **fluctuate:** normalized random time duration added for each mailing step, including the first message.**fluctuate:** normalized random time duration added for each mailing step, including the first message.
- **expire:** time duration, after all the messages have been sent, to keep the letter and message records in the database before they are deleted.**expire:** time duration, after all the messages have been sent, to keep the letter and message records in the database before they are deleted.


Context
-------

Template execution context contains the following fields:


- **Frontmatter:** the raw Markdown frontmatter as `map[string]any`.**Frontmatter:** the raw Markdown frontmatter as `map[string]any`.
- **Recipient:** the raw message target as `map[string]any`. It
will contain `name` and `email` fields and any other fields
fromt the contact source.**Recipient:** the raw message target as `map[string]any`. Itwill contain `name` and `email` fields and any other fieldsfromt the contact source.
- **Content:** rendered Markdown body.**Content:** rendered Markdown body.
- **Schedule:****Schedule:**


